description:
The **PLUMMY** team lives by the spirit of harmony and a burning desire to bring joyful innovations and enjoyable experiences to our players. Our goal is to provide them with comfort, calmness, and sincere fun!


If you're a skilled UI/UX specialist ready to join our growing team, let’s connect! In this role, you'll be the mastermind behind designing and bringing to life intuitive, captivating user experiences for our mobile f2p project Star Merge. Let's merge your talents with our vision and create something truly magical!


**Responsibilities:**

* Collaborate with the game development team to understand project requirements and translate them into effective UI/UX designs;
* Create prototypes to visualize design concepts and gather feedback from stakeholders;
* Conduct user research and testing to inform design decisions and improve user experience;
* Design and prototype user interfaces using Adobe Photoshop;
* Work with game designers and developers to implement designs in a timely and efficient manner;
* Continuously iterate on designs based on user feedback and data analytics;
* Stay up-to-date on industry trends and best practices in UI/UX design.

**Requirements:**

* 3+ years of experience in UI/UX design for mobile games;
* Released game projects;
* Strong collaboration and communication skills, with the ability to work effectively in a remote team environment;
* Strong design skills, with a portfolio demonstrating a deep understanding of user-centered design principles;
* Proficiency in Photoshop, experience with Figma is an advantage;
* Experience with prototyping and user testing;
* Knowledge of current trends and best practices in mobile game design and development;
* Knowledge of Unity, Cocos game engines;
* Proficiency in both written and spoken English communication.

**Nice to have, but not necessary:**

* Academic education in graphic design, UX design, or a related field.

**What we offer:**

* Competitive salaries, reviewed on a timely basis, or personal achievements and involvement in the project;
* Full social package, and medical assurance according to IT Park Moldova for office employees;
* 5 sick days, 28 calendar days of vacation;
* Working in a team of talented and passionate professionals, with the ability for fast growth in professional terms;
* Five days full-time, flexible working hours.


If you're passionate about designing user experiences that engage and delight mobile game players, we'd love to hear from you. Please submit your resume and a link to your portfolio to be considered for this opportunity at Plummy Games.
